 babies pretend to go to school.\n\n''Song'': Mary Had a Baby Duck (Mary Had a Little Lamb)\n\nGranny leaves and lets [[Bugs Bunny|Bugs]] be in charge since he's the oldest, but Taz goes missing.\n|LineColor=FFFFBF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=The Creature from the Chocolate Chip / Card Bored Box\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2001|9|19}}\n|DirectedBy=\n|WrittenBy= Carter Crocker<hr>Michael Maler & Obie Scott Wade\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=Karl Geurs<hr>Tom Minton\n|EpisodeNumber=4\n|EpisodeNumber2=4\n|ShortSummary=Sylvester eats all the cookies and [[Daffy Duck|Daffy]] tells Granny a monster did it.\n\n''Song'': The Looney Riddle (The Riddle Song)\n\nGranny gives Bugs, Daffy, Tweety and Lola a box to play in. They don't like it at first, then they fight over whose game is better, using the box to play in, at the end it works for all their games.\n|LineColor=FFFFBF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Time and Time Again / May the Best Taz Win\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2001|9|23}}\n|DirectedBy=\n|WrittenBy= Michael Maler & Obie Scott Wade<hr>Karl Geurs\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=Tom Minton<hr>Karl Geurs\n|EpisodeNumber=5\n|EpisodeNumber2=5\n|ShortSummary=Granny teaches the babies to tell the time.\n\n''Song'': Does Your Tongue Hang Low? (Do Your Ears Hang Low)\n\nBugs and Daffy fight over who's getting Lola on their badminton team.\n|LineColor=FFFFBF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Mine! / Sylvester the Pester\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2001|9|26}}\n|DirectedBy=\n|WrittenBy= [[Christopher Simmons]]<hr>[[David Slack]]\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=Tom Minton\n|EpisodeNumber=6\n|EpisodeNumber2=6\n|ShortSummary=Daffy steals Granny's wallet and claims it as his own.\n\n''Song'': Over the Burrow (Over the Meadow)\nSylvester keeps trying to stay out of bed just so he can spend some time with Granny.\n|LineColor=FFFFBF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Cat-Taz-Trophy / Duck! Monster! Duck!\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2001|9|28}}\n|DirectedBy=\n|WrittenBy= Roger Eschbacher<hr>Julie McNally-Cahill & Timothy Cahill\n|Aux