d meets the star Willy Worm himself.\n|LineColor=7B26CA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Bend it Like Petunia / Cock-a-Doodle-Doo-It!\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|9|05}}\n|EpisodeNumber=49\n|EpisodeNumber2=9\n|ShortSummary=Floyd introduces the babies to a game of soccer, Daffy under the impression girls can't play it and Petunia and Taz with a better sportsmanship than the others. Petunia manages to score the game to a draw.\n\n''Song'': He'll Be Zooming Around the Mountain (She'll Be Coming 'Round the Mountain)\n\nFloyd takes the babies to a farm. Tweety is met by a depressed [[Foghorn Leghorn|Foghorn]] who is mocked by all the other roosters for his difference. The babies help him to gain spirit and courage and he befriends both [[Barnyard Dawg]] and the other roosters.\n|LineColor=7B26CA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Wrong! / Win, Lose or Daffy\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|9|15}}\n|EpisodeNumber=50\n|EpisodeNumber2=10\n|ShortSummary=The babies go with Floyd to pick apples. Melissa lectures the others on correctly picking the apples which annoys them, although she can't understand their reaction. Everyone shows their methods are not wrong but different.\n\n''Song'': Looney Loo (Here We Go Looby Loo)\n\nFloyd takes the babies to a mini-golf course. Finding himself without a chance of winning, Daffy cheats, whilst Tweety scores down the hole every time. Daffy realises the game lies more in the fun than the winning score.\n|LineColor=7B26CA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=A Turtle Named Myrtle / There's Nothing Like a Good Book\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|9|27}}\n|EpisodeNumber=51\n|EpisodeNumber2=11\n|ShortSummary=On a day at the beach, Melissa gets frustrated that she can't have a new spade and makes friends with a baby turtle she calls Myrtle. Melissa wants to keep her, but learns she can't take her from her natural habitat\n\n''Note'' is this the one hundred episode of the serie\n\n''Song'': Oh My Daring, [[Wile E. Coyote and the Road Runner|Coyote]] (Oh My Darling, Clementine)\n\nBugs, Daffy, and Lola argue what the material of the moon is. Floyd takes them and Taz to the library for research. They find hard to refrain from making noise, but they manage to find the information they were looking for.\n|LineColor=7B26CA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=The Dolly Vanishes / Duck's Reflucks\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|10|01}}\n|EpisodeNumber=52\n|EpisodeNumber2=12\n|ShortSummary=Granny takes the babies on a train to travel to Floyd's college. When Lola loses her doll Edna, she interrogates the others for their stories. Floyd reveals Edna has half shut in the train window.\n\nFloyd takes the babies to the green screen for their picture to be taken. Daffy, disappointed at the choice of scene, spoils Bugs' appearances on the green screen until the photographer gets his priorities right.\n\n''Song'': [[Pep\u00e9 Le Pew|Vive Le Pew]], Le Skunk {{in lang|fr}} (Vive La Compagnie)\n|LineColor=7B26CA\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Stop and Smell Up the Flowers / Firehouse Frolics\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|10|16}}\n|EpisodeNumber=53\n|EpisodeNumber2=13\n|ShortSummary=Pepe tours the babies around the Acme gardens finding a place to plant a lemon tree. Eventually everyone gets irritated by Pepe's stink, upsetting him, but they rejoin him and he introduces them to his pal [[Gossamer (Looney Tunes)|Gossamer]].\n\n''Song'': Loonies Turn Around (Windmills Turn Around)\n\nFloyd takes the babies to the fire station where Captain Frank tutors them on safety procedures, but Daffy won't follow the rules. However Daffy's morale in the situation of a fire is higher than all the others.\n'''Note''': This is the series finale.\n\n|LineColor=7B26CA\n}}\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List of Baby Looney Tunes episodes}}\n[[Category:Lists of American children's animated television series episodes|Baby Looney Tunes]]\n", "name_user": "210.186.78.24", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.